1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the construction and analysis of a binary cyclic code, which involves coding theory and information theory. 
2. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The Gold and Kasami Welch APN power functions are commonly used in cryptography, and the paper may have implications for the security of cryptographic systems. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper may involve the use of algorithms and data structures in the construction and analysis of the cyclic code. 
4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper may have implications for the use of error-correcting codes in network communication and data transmission. 
5. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - Similar to cs.SI, the paper may have implications for the use of error-correcting codes in network communication and data transmission.
